'''Imperial Army troopers''' were the standard [[Infantry/Legends|infantry]] of the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]] and the most common [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] on many subject [[Planet/Legends|worlds]]. Following the Empire's post-[[Battle of Endor/Legends|Endor]] fragmentation, their numbers were maintained by periodic conscription of subject populations.

==Characteristics==
Imperial Army [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]] were recruited from all across the Empire, though preferably from worlds which lacked any [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|rebel]] sympathies. Those who passed their initial screening at their local [[Imperial Recruitment Office]] and the medical and intelligence assessments at a [[Training Center]] were shipped to one of the thousands of drop camps situated across the Empire for basic training. Physical fitness, equipment maintenance, team-building drills, and indoctrination were all part of training to become an Army trooper. Though survival in a variety of environments was standard, some drop camps specialized in certain exotic types as well. All manner of combat techniques were taught, from hand-to-hand fighting and blaster proficiency to grenade and heavy weapons training.<ref name="ISB2">[[Imperial Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''Imperial Sourcebook'', Second Edition]]</ref>

Troopers fresh out of training were reasonably professional soldiers, though lacking in experience and, among those who were conscripted, generally low morale. While capable of facing regular [[Rebel trooper/Legends|Rebel troopers]] in combat, they were easy prey for the [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Alliance's SpecForce]]. Those who managed to survive a few tours of duty, mostly career soldiers, were able to hone their skills to a greater degree and likewise possessed superior morale and confidence in their abilities. Such veteran troopers were a fairly significant threat even to SpecForce. The most elite of the Army were [[Imperial Army Special Missions trooper/Legends|Special Missions troopers]].<ref name="Spec">''[[Rules of Engagement: The Rebel SpecForce Handbook]]''</ref>

However, military duty for an Army trooper was relatively light: whereas the [[Stormtrooper Corps/Legends|Stormtrooper Corps]]&mdash;which was separate from the Imperial Army&mdash;was employed for boarding actions and attacking enemy positions, regular army troopers were used to secure ground already taken. They also maintained Imperial military bases or served aboard fleet vessels as marines, and garrisoned pacified worlds.<ref name="Rebellion Era Campaign Guide">''[[Rebellion Era Campaign Guide]]''</ref> Troopers were more than willing to fight when necessary though; thirty troopers participated in an attack against a group of [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]] in the [[Whistler's Whirlpool Tapcafe]] on [[Trogan/Legends|Trogan]] in [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]].<ref name="TLC">''[[The Last Command]]''</ref>

At some point in the history of the [[Fel Empire]], the Stormtrooper Corps was disbanded and the stormtroopers were redistributed into the ranks of the Imperial Army. Yet individual stormtrooper units continued to operate separately from army troopers as elite shock forces, and thus they retained their [[Stormtrooper armor/Legends|armor]] as well.<ref name="Legacy0">[[Star Wars: Legacy (2006) 0|''Star Wars: Legacy'' (2006) 0]]</ref>

==Equipment==
[[File:Imperial_Trooper_Deployment.jpg|right|200px|Army troopers in combat]]
During the early years of the Empire, troopers wore a similar uniform as [[Imperial Navy Trooper/Legends|Imperial Navy troopers]], though it was grey-colored, along with partial [[field armor]] and a blast helmet with integrated [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]] like the [[DH77 headcomm/Legends|DH77 headcomm]]. Standard gear consisted of a [[Blaster rifle/Legends|blaster rifle]], usually an [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifle]] and [[Grenade/Legends|grenades]] along with survival gear and a utility belt containing supplies.<ref name="ISB2" /><ref name="Spec" /> Goggles were also worn, with a variety of tinted and vision-enhancing models in use by the army.<ref name="Classic Adventures: Volume Four — The Best of the Journal">''[[Classic Adventures: Volume Four — The Best of the Journal]]''</ref> Troopers could be equipped or operated as part of the crew for an [[Heavy weapon|infantry support weapon]], including [[Light repeating blaster/Legends|light repeating blasters]], [[Equalizer]] ion cannons, [[PLX-2M portable missile launcher]]s, [[DEMP gun/Legends|DEMP guns]], [[CSPL-12 projectile launcher/Legends|CSPL-12]] projectile launchers, or [[E-Web heavy repeating blaster/Legends|E-Web heavy repeating blasters]].<ref name="ISB2" /> They also had similarities in uniform to the [[Vehicle Command Crewer]]s, more specifically the Armored Cavalry Division.

The standard Imperial Army backpack carried tents, rations, 1.5 liter water canteens, excavation tools, and other gear.<ref name="Dangerous Covenants">''[[Dangerous Covenants]]''</ref>

