==Variants==
*[[Imperial Army Special Missions trooper/Legends|Special Missions troopers]] were the elite special forces of the Imperial Army.

*[[Land assault trooper|Assault troopers]] were the mechanized infantry units of the Imperial Army trained to operate a variety of land war machines.

*[[Swamp trooper/Legends|Swamp troopers]] were a division of the Imperial Army tasked with operating in [[Swamp/Legends|swamp]] environments.

*[[Imperial medic/Legends|Imperial medics]] were personnel attached to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] ground and naval forces that had specialized medical training.

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:ImperialMedic_TFU_Wii.jpg|thumb|An [[Imperial medic/Legends|Imperial medic]] from the [[video game]] ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]'']]
[[Imperial medic/Legends|Imperial medics]], as well as [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officers]], wore field uniforms similar to that of regular Army Troopers.

The [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officers]] in ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'' armor resembles Imperial Army Trooper armor.

In the [[2003]] [[video game]] [[Star Wars Galaxies|''Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided'']], certain Imperial [[Wikipedia:Non-player character|non-player characters]] were identified as Imperial troopers, and wore white jumpsuits, with a white belt, boots, and gloves. Given that these Imperial troopers acted as soldiers who patrolled Imperial bases on various worlds, it can be deduced that these were simply Imperial Army troopers wearing a different type of uniform.

Despite them being the most numerous of the Empire's soldiers, they are rarely seen in any Star Wars media. This can be seen as mostly coming from the fact that the Imperial Army Troopers are primarily a garrison force securing planets faraway from frontlines where combat is uncommon and thus the superior training of the stormtroopers would be wasted, while most of Star Wars media is set closer to the frontlines, where stormtroopers are more common.

