{{Quote|A Jedi sufficiently strong in the Force can be trained to produce a facsimile, but not true Sith lightning.|[[Darth Plagueis/Legends|Darth Plagueis]]|<ref name="Darth Plagueis (novel)">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref>}}
'''Electric Judgment''', also known as '''Emerald Lightning''', was a light side [[Force power/Legends|Force technique]] used to spray electric bolts of variable intensity from the hands and fingers. At one time, it was classified as a forbidden [[The Force/Legends|Force]] power within the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]; however, some Jedi such as [[Plo Koon/Legends|Plo Koon]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], and [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] practiced it.

==Description==
Electric Judgment,<ref name="JBPG">[[Star Wars: Episode I Jedi Power Battles: Prima's Official Strategy Guide|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Jedi Power Battles'': Prima's Official Strategy Guide]]</ref><ref name="Jedi vs. Sith" /> also known as Emerald Lightning, was a Force power used by the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to spray electric bolts of variable intensity from the hands and fingers.<ref name="Jedi Path" /> It manifested as [[Color/Legends|yellow-orange]],<ref name="Jedi Power Battles">[[Star Wars: Episode I Jedi Power Battles|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Jedi Power Battles'']]</ref> green,<ref name="The Unifying Force">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force]]''</ref> white,<ref name=":0">''[[Champions of the Force]]''</ref> or golden lightning<ref name=":1">[[Crucible (novel)|''Crucible'']]</ref> instead of blue<ref name="Dark Force Rising Sourcebook">''[[Dark Force Rising Sourcebook]]''</ref> but otherwise it was very similar in both appearance and usage to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] Force power known as [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]].<ref name="Jedi Path" />

==Applications==
One common difference between the Jedi's use of Electric Judgment and the Sith's use of Force lightning was that the Jedi's application came from a sense of determined justice.<ref name="Jedi Path" /> However, on at least one occasion this [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side]] power was channeled using a Jedi's anger.<ref name="Destiny's Way">''[[The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way]]''</ref> Like Force lightning, it had to be channeled through living flesh, and could be used [[Death/Legends|lethally]],<ref name="The Unifying Force" /> but often it was used to stun or knock opponents unconscious.<ref name="Jedi vs. Sith" /> The energies of Electric Judgment could be contained in a [[Kinetite/Legends|kinetite]], a ball of pure kinetic force.<ref name="Jedi Path" /> They could also be used as a shield against attack,<ref name="The Unifying Force" /> or unleashed as chain lightning.<ref name="Destiny's Way" /> Electric Judgment could be blocked by the use of a sufficiently powerful [[protection bubble]].<ref name="Star Wars: Force and Destiny Core Rulebook">[[Star Wars: Force and Destiny Core Rulebook|''Star Wars: Force and Destiny'' Core Rulebook]]</ref> As a form of Force lightning, this power could strike, and thus [[Stun/Legends|stun]]<ref name="Destiny's Way" /> or kill [[Yuuzhan Vong]] despite their nature as being considered absent from the Force.<ref name="The Unifying Force" />

==Users==
Among the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], this Force ability was uncommon and controversial due to its association with anger and aggression and its similarity to Force lightning. It was even featured on [[Jedi Seer]] [[Sabla-Mandibu]]'s list of "Forbidden Force Techniques" and classified as prohibited to [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]]. A few [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] such as [[Plo Koon/Legends|Plo Koon]], however, did study the technique under controlled conditions, a practice that had been occurring since at least 990 BBY.<ref name="Jedi Path" /> During Exar Kun's physical last stand and defeat, the Jedi Order massed against him and by pooling the power of the whole order, conjured a shield of light while raining down large lightning bolts on him, even as Kun tried to ascend to a more powerful form. The clash of darkness and light ravaged the planet and halted Kun's ambitions.<ref name="Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War 6">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War 6|''Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War'' 6]]</ref> When the Separatists rose up, some Jedi such as those who were champions or warriors of the light, utilized this Force power.<ref>[[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures (video game)|''Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures'' {{C|video game}}]]</ref> Yoda was practitioner, employing it during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]],<ref name="Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Who Are the Jedi?">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Who Are the Jedi?]]''</ref> to burn away a dark reflection of himself with a touch,<ref name="TCW:Destiny">{{TCW|Destiny (The Clone Wars)}}</ref> and [[Skirmish in the Senate|against the Sith]].<ref>[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' {{C|novelization}}]]</ref>

During a mission to capture the criminal known as [[Dreed Pommel]], Plo Koon confronted [[Gender/Legends|him]] at a suite in the city of [[Ektra]], [[Metellos/Legends|Metellos]]. Pommel had taken a [[Claria Labreezle|young girl]] hostage and killed her entire family. During this encounter, Koon let out a barrage of lightning at Pommel's head that also disarmed him and then a second burst of lightning that knocked him unconscious. He immediately reported this incident to the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] and stated that he had not felt any anger or fear as he let out the blast of Force lightning but was indeed calm and in control of his emotions, nor was he tempted to kill his opponent once he had subdued the criminal. Therefore, he was able to conclude he was acting according to the will of the Force. The Council asked him to contemplate whether he felt it was wrong of him to have utilized its power during the mission and whether he would use it again. After much [[Meditation/Legends|meditation]], Koon concluded that it would be wrong of him to ignore its power, as Claria Labreezle's survival showed, and that he should develop it into a useful technique. As requested by the Council, he recorded his experiences with the Force lightning that he dubbed "Electric Judgment" on the [[Great Holocron/Legends|Great Holocron]].<ref name="Jedi vs. Sith" />

[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] utilized the kinetite technique, akin to this power, on [[Mimban/Legends|Mimban]],<ref name="Jedi Path" /> while in close proximity to the [[Kaiburr crystal]]<ref name="Rise and Fall">''[[The Rise and Fall of Darth Vader]]''</ref> as he attempted to subdue [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]].<ref name="Splinter">''[[Splinter of the Mind's Eye]]''</ref> In 11 ABY on Yavin 4, when Luke Skywalker’s students found the strength and understanding for a final showdown with the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] who had been oppressing them, the first class of the New Jedi Order used the light side to sear [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]] with lightning while simultaneously caging him with light and wind, defeating his [[Force ghost/Legends|spirit]] and saving their [[Jedi Master/Legends|master]].<ref name=":0" /> [[Anakin Solo]] used Electric Judgment when he was [[Oneness/Legends|consumed]] by the light side of the Force [[Mission to Myrkr|just before his death]], with streams of lightning arcing from his [[Limb/Legends|limbs]] into his [[Warrior caste|enemies]].<ref name="Star by Star">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref> While [[Battle of Ebaq|fighting]] on [[Ebaq 9]], [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] struck multiple targets at once with the power,<ref name="Destiny's Way" /> similar to the refinement of Force lightning known as [[Force lightning/Legends#Force storm|Force Storm]].<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref> He later used this power as a shield of electricity against enemy lightning during the reconquest of Coruscant.<ref name="The Unifying Force" />

[[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] Luke Skywalker used this power aboard [[Shimrra's Citadel]] during the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar|battle]] against [[Shimrra Jamaane]] in [[29 ABY/Legends|29 ABY]] to save his [[Jaina Solo Fel|niece]] and nephew from the [[Slayers]]; his powerful version sent sparks of green lighting coruscating over the body of a Slayer, instantly killing him and causing his body to convulse.<ref name="The Unifying Force" /> However, even this attack of the Grandmaster's could be resisted by someone skilled in [[Tutaminis]], as shown when [[Abeloth]] was able to resist it with no harm more severe than being pushed back slightly when Skywalker [[Battle in the Fallanassi village|used it against her in]] 44 ABY.<ref name="Vortex">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Vortex]]''</ref> In 45 ABY, Luke Skywalker, along with his [[Twin/Legends|sister]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], used this power while within a [[Unidentified monolith|monolith]] to weave shells of defensive golden lightning.<ref name=":1" />

[[Jaden Korr]] used this power [[Mission to the frozen moon|against]] [[Alpha (clone)|Alpha]] in [[41 ABY]].<ref name="Riptide">[[Riptide (novel)|''Riptide'']]</ref> Later, in 41 ABY, upon seeing a [[Hologram/Legends|hologram]] of Jaden Korr defending himself with this power, [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] [[Darth Wyyrlok (I)|Wyyrlok]] claimed that this power was conjured out of fear and implied Jaden was tempted by the dark side.<ref name="Riptide" /> It is not clear if this was an accurate assessment, as Wyyrlok mistakenly<ref name="The Unifying Force" /> believed that what he saw was just a variant of dark side lightning.<ref name="Riptide" />

